Surface kernel auto-update installer
=====================================

The majority of this project was generated by Claude (Anthropic's Claude Code)
at the direction of the repository maintainer, who configured, tested, and
maintains it. The maintainer does not claim authorship of the generated
scripts. Commits are co-authored accordingly:

    Co-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>

This project only automates building/installing two kernel packages and
bundles no kernel source of its own. It additionally publishes the resulting
binary packages as a signed pacman repository ([surface-cachyos]) via this
repository's GitHub Releases; those binaries are unmodified builds of the
packages credited below. The packages it builds, and where credit
for the actual kernel patches belongs:

  - Steefzar/linux-cachyos-surface        — fork of linux-surface/linux-surface
                                             with CachyOS packaging added; tracks
                                             linux-surface's official patches
  - Steefzar/linux-cachyos-surface-latest — same, tracking the newest CachyOS
                                             release, with a best-effort
                                             hand-rebase fallback when
                                             linux-surface hasn't caught up yet
  - linux-surface/linux-surface           — Microsoft Surface kernel patches;
                                             the only external upstream either
                                             package depends on
  - CachyOS/linux-cachyos, CachyOS/linux  — the CachyOS kernel base and
                                             packaging conventions

Historical note: this setup originally tracked dylandhall/linux-cachyos-surface
(itself forked from jonpetersathan/linux-cachyos-surface) as a single combined
upstream for both the patches and the packaging scripts. It now maintains its
own packaging directly on top of linux-surface, credited above, so that it's
no longer dependent on a third party re-publishing new versions -- prior art
and thanks to both projects regardless.
